  "local_port": 53454,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best books for bank exam?",
  "response": "There are several highly recommended books for bank exam preparation that can help you cover various sections of the exam, such as Quantitative Aptitude, Reasoning, English Language, and General Awareness. Here are some of the best books for each section:\n\n### Quantitative Aptitude:\n1. **\"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\" by R.S. Aggarwal**\n   - This book is comprehensive and covers all the necessary topics with a variety of practice questions.\n\n2. **\"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\" by Rajesh Varma**\n   - Known for its quick methods and shortcuts, this book is excellent for those looking to improve their speed and accuracy.\n\n### Reasoning:\n1. **\"A Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning\" by R.S. Aggarwal**\n   - This is a go-to book for reasoning, covering both verbal and non-verbal reasoning sections comprehensively.\n\n2. **\"Analytical Reasoning\" by M.K. Pandey**\n   - This book is useful for analytical reasoning and puzzle-solving techniques.\n\n### English Language:\n1. **\"Objective General English\" by S.P. Bakshi**\n   - A thorough book that covers grammar, vocabulary, and comprehension, with ample practice questions.\n\n2. **\"Word Power Made Easy\" by Norman Lewis**\n   - Excellent for improving vocabulary, which is crucial for the English section of bank exams.\n\n### General Awareness:\n1. **\"Banking Awareness\" by Arihant Publications**\n   - Focuses on banking and financial awareness, which is very relevant for bank exams.\n\n2. **\"Lucent\u2019s General Knowledge\" by Dr. Binay Karna and R.P. Suman**\n   - A comprehensive book for general knowledge that covers a wide range of topics.\n\n### Practice Sets and Mock Tests:\n1. **\"20 Practice Sets for IBPS PO/ MT Preliminary Examination\" by Disha Experts**\n   - Contains practice sets that mimic the actual exam format, helping you gauge your preparation level.\n\n2. **\"IBPS Bank Clerk Preliminary & Main CWE 20 Practice Sets\" by GKP**\n   - Another good resource for practicing with simulated test papers.\n\nIt\u2019s important to use these books alongside other resources like online mock tests and current affairs updates to stay well-prepared. Good luck with your exam preparation!",
